					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Vellum codex, Italian semi-cursive script, unpunctuated, of 14th century.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="perg">
								<support>Parchment codex.</support>
								<extent rend="visible">422 folios <dimensions unit="mm" type="leaf">
										<height>234</height>
										<width>165</width>
									</dimensions>
									<dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
										<height>164</height>
										<width>125</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<foliation>
									<p>422 folios (+ 5 modern paper flyleaves at the beginning and 4 at the end).</p>
								</foliation>
								<collation>
									<p>Quires of  mostly 10 leaves each.</p>
									<p>Quires signed with Hebrew letters at the beginning and at the end, also marked with catchwords at the end.</p>
									<p>Running titles in the upper margins, occasionally cut off.</p>
								</collation>
								<condition>
									<p>Defective at the end.</p>
									<p>Side margins are too closely cut and some of the marginal notes are not fully preserved.</p>
									<p>On folio 422v ink has nearly entirely faded.</p>
								</condition>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout ruledLines="31" writtenLines="31" columns="1">
									<p>Hair-side and flesh-side of the folio is discernible.</p>
									<p>Visible hard-point ruling.</p>
									<p>Some omissions supplied in the margins.</p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
						</objectDesc>
						<handDesc hands="2">
							<summary>Italian semi-cursive script, unpunctuated, of 14th century.</summary>
							<handNote script="Hebrew" scope="sole">
								<p>
									<locus from="408r" to="422v"/>due to a different hand.</p>
							</handNote>
						</handDesc>
						<additions>
							<p>An index of commentaries from c17th century is given on folio 419v.</p>
							<p>A note of purchase of the manuscript, 18th or 19th century, folio 1v.</p>
							<p>
								<name type="person" role="owner">M. Conti</name>: inscribed in a note of purchase, folio 3r, with a date of <date calendar="Gregorian">8 January 1836</date>.</p>
							<p>
								<name type="person" role="owner">Yehudah ben Benyamin ha-Menaḳed ben Yo'av</name>, probably also the scribe: inscribed in a contract of sale, folio 419v. Yehudah bar Benyamin sold the manuscript to Rabi Natan and Rabi Avraham, sons of Rabi Yeḥiel, son of Daniel of Monte Santo, for 15 gold florins.</p>
						</additions>
						<bindingDesc>
							<binding>
								<p>Pre-1600, black leather. Boxed.</p>
								<p>Spine: 'Bible Commentaries Various Authors. Hebrew. Brit. Mus. Additional Ms. 24896.'</p>
							</binding>
						</bindingDesc>
